text: Tyrese Jay Francois (born 16 July 2000) is an Australian professional soccer player who plays as a midfielder for Premier League side Fulham. ==Early life== Tyrese was born in Campbelltown, New South Wales, located on the outskirts of the metropolitan area of Sydney, Australia. At the age of 5, he joined Campbelltown Uniting Church Soccer Club and later moved to Camden Tigers. In 2013, Tyrese and his family moved to London, England, where he joined the Fulham F.C. Academy system. ==Career== On 27 August 2019, he made his professional debut for Fulham in an EFL Cup tie against Southampton. ==References== ==External links== * Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Australian soccer players Category:Association football midfielders Category:Australian people of Mauritian descent Category:Fulham F.C. players
